{"COMPACT":[{"def":"Joined or held together; leagued; confederated.","pos":""},{"def":"Composed or made; -- with of.","pos":""}],"COMPACTED":[{"def":"Compact; pressed close; concentrated; firmly united.","pos":""}],"COMPACTEDLY":[{"def":"In a compact manner.","pos":""}],"COMPACTEDNESS":[{"def":"A state of being compact.","pos":""}],"COMPACTER":[{"def":"One who makes a compact.","pos":""}],"COMPACTIBLE":[{"def":"That may be compacted.","pos":""}],"COMPACTION":[{"def":"The act of making compact, or the state of being compact.","pos":""}],"COMPACTLY":[{"def":"In a compact manner; with close union of parts; densely; tersely.","pos":""}],"COMPACTNESS":[{"def":"The state or quality of being compact; close union of parts; density.","pos":""}],"COMPACTURE":[{"def":"Close union or connection of parts; manner of joining; construction.","pos":""}],"COMPAGES":[{"def":"A system or structure of many parts united.","pos":""}],"COMPAGINATE":[{"def":"To unite or hold together; as, the side pieces compaginate the frame.","pos":""}],"COMPAGINATION":[{"def":"Union of parts; structure.","pos":""}],"COMPANABLE":[{"def":"Companionable; sociable.","pos":""}],"COMPANATOR":[{"def":"Same as Impanator.","pos":""}],"COMPANIABLE":[{"def":"Companionable; sociable.","pos":""}],"COMPANION":[{"def":"One who accompanies or is in company with another for a longer or shorter period, either from choice or casually; one who is much in the company of, or is associated with, another or others; an associate; a comrade; a consort; a partner.","pos":""},{"def":"A knight of the lowest rank in certain orders; as, a companion of the Bath.","pos":""}],"COMPANIONABLE":[{"def":"Fitted to be a companion; fit for good fellowship; agreeable; sociable.","pos":""}],"COMPANIONLESS":[{"def":"Without a companion.","pos":""}],"COMPANIONSHIP":[{"def":"Fellowship; association; the act or fact of keeping company with any one.","pos":""}],"COMPANY":[{"def":"A subdivision of a regiment of troops under the command of a captain, numbering in the United States (full strength) 100 men.","pos":""},{"def":"The crew of a ship, including the officers; as, a whole ship's company.","pos":""}],"COMPARABLE":[{"def":"Capable of being compared; worthy of comparison.","pos":""}],"COMPARATE":[{"def":"One of two things compared together.","pos":""}],"COMPARATION":[{"def":"A making ready; provision.","pos":""}],"COMPARATIVE":[{"def":"Expressing a degree greater or less than the positive degree of the quality denoted by an adjective or adverb.","pos":""}],"COMPARATIVELY":[{"def":"According to estimate made by comparison; relatively; not positively or absolutely.","pos":""}],"COMPARATOR":[{"def":"An instrument or machine for comparing anything to be measured with a standard measure; -- applied especially to a machine for comparing standards of length.","pos":""}],"COMPARE":[{"def":"To examine the character or qualities of, as of two or more persons or things, for the purpose of discovering their resemblances or differences; to bring into comparison; to regard with discriminating attention.","pos":""},{"def":"To represent as similar, for the purpose of illustration; to liken.","pos":""}],"COMPARER":[{"def":"One who compares.","pos":""}],"COMPARISON":[{"def":"The modification, by inflection or otherwise, which the adjective and adverb undergo to denote degrees of quality or quantity; as, little, less, least, are examples of comparison.","pos":""},{"def":"A figure by which one person or thing is compared to another, or the two are considered with regard to some property or quality, which is common to them both; e.","pos":""}],"COMPART":[{"def":"To divide; to mark out into parts or subdivisions.","pos":""}],"COMPARTITION":[{"def":"The act of dividing into parts or compartments; division; also, a division or compartment.","pos":""}],"COMPARTMENT":[{"def":"One of the sections into which the hold of a ship is divided by water-tight bulkheads.","pos":""}],"COMPASS":[{"def":"The range of notes, or tones, within the capacity of a voice or instument.","pos":""}],"COMPASSABLE":[{"def":"Capable of being compassed or accomplished.","pos":""}],"COMPASSED":[{"def":"Rounded; arched.","pos":""}],"COMPASSES":[{"def":"An instrument for describing circles, measuring figures, etc.","pos":""}],"COMPASSING":[{"def":"Curved; bent; as, compassing timbers.","pos":""}],"COMPASSION":[{"def":"Literally, suffering with another; a sensation of sorrow excited by the distress or misfortunes of another; pity; commiseration.","pos":""}],"COMPASSIONABLE":[{"def":"Deserving compassion or pity; pitiable.","pos":""}],"COMPASSIONATE":[{"def":"Having a temper or disposition to pity; sympathetic; merciful.","pos":""},{"def":"Complaining; inviting pity; pitiable.","pos":""}],"COMPASSIONATELY":[{"def":"In a compassionate manner; mercifully.","pos":""}],"COMPASSIONATENESS":[{"def":"The quality or state of being compassionate.","pos":""}],"COMPASSLESS":[{"def":"Having no compass.","pos":""}],"COMPATERNITY":[{"def":"The relation of a godfather to a person.","pos":""}],"COMPATIBILITY":[{"def":"The quality or power of being compatible or congruous; congruity; as, a compatibility of tempers; a compatibility of properties.","pos":""}],"COMPATIBLE":[{"def":"Capable of existing in harmony; congruous; suitable; not repugnant; -- usually followed by with.","pos":""}],"COMPATIBLENESS":[{"def":"Compatibility; consistency; fitness; agreement.","pos":""}],"COMPATIBLY":[{"def":"In a compatible manner.","pos":""}],"COMPATIENT":[{"def":"Suffering or enduring together.","pos":""}],"COMPATRIOT":[{"def":"One of the same country, and having like interests and feeling.","pos":""}],"COMPATRIOTISM":[{"def":"The condition of being compatriots.","pos":""}]}